CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper August 24, 1946, pg. 28, reads: "Wives Entertained - Members of the Troop Committee of the Brownsville Boy Scouts entertained their wives last Sunday afternoon in Pittsburgh. The group visited the YMCA, The Pittsburgh Courier, and several other community organizations. Left to right, seated, are Mmes. Ethel Doughtery, Durce Jackson, George Jackson, Clarence Patterson, Miss Felecia Thompson, Mrs. Eugene Hancock, Mrs. Dennis Colmes; standing, Clarence Jackson, Durce Jackson, George Jackson, Clarence Patterson, Russell Mason, Eugene Hancock and Dennis Colmes. The visitors attended services at Ebenezer Baptist Church. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Members of Troop Committee of Brownsville Boy Scouts and wives, including seated from left: Ethel Doughtery, Mrs. Jackson, Mrs. Jackson, Mrs. Patterson, Felecia Thompson, Mrs. Hancock, Mrs. Colmes; standing: Clarence Jackson, Durce Jackson, George Jackson, Clarence Patterson, Russell Mason, Eugene Hancock and Dennis Colmes. gathered behind table in Centre Avenue YMCA with Henry O. Tanner painting "Christ and His Mother" in background
